Resource Management
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This work is about integrating resource management systems.
 The systems which will be dealt with have, for the most part, previously
 been mentioned.
 This brings us to the next item for discussion: resource management.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Resource management can broadly be defined in terms similar to the four
 basic functions of persistent data storage: creation, reading, updating,
 and deletion of resources (CRUD
\begin_inset CommandInset nomenclature
LatexCommand nomenclature
symbol "CRUD"
description "Creation, Reading, Updating, and Deletion"

\end_inset

)
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
